# This file lists commit hashes that `git blame` should skip when attributing lines.
# It prevents global formatting changes (e.g., full-repo ruff reformats) from
# making every line appear authored by the formatting commit. Git reads this
# file when `blame.ignoreRevsFile` is set in git config.
#
# Usage:
#   git config blame.ignoreRevsFile .git-blame-ignore-revs
#   or: git blame --ignore-revs-file .git-blame-ignore-revs <file>
#
# Add the full SHA of any commit that made only formatting/mechanical changes
# across many files (e.g., ruff format, line-length changes, import sorting).
# One hash per line; comments and blank lines are allowed.
#
# 4ce1bcf7 -- "Apply Black formatter to entire codebase"
#   Ran Black across every file, making blame point at this commit
#   for almost every line instead of the original author. This is the
#   exact kind of commit this file exists to skip.
#
# When adding future global mechanical changes (e.g., enabling ruff
# format in CI, import sorting, line-length changes), add those
# commit hashes here too.
